1) mkdir directory_name
2) sudo apt install git //Install git
3) sud apt install vim  //Install vim
4) git config --global user.email "email address"
4) git config --global user.name "name"
5) You can use SSH or https
   -To use ssh -> Create public key to use ssh Follow instructions on https://help.github.com/articles/signing-commits-with-gpg/
6) Install npm and npm (https://github.com/creationix/nvm)
7) Install node nvm install node.
8) Install Heroku CLI (Requires an account)
  --npm install -g heroku-cli
  or
  --wget -q0- https://cli-assets.heroku.com/install-ubuntu.sh | sh
9) install Text Editor
10) Install Rails...



  
